OVERVIEW: Add a synchronized folder that maintains sync with filesystem

USAGE: xcodeproj-cli add-sync-folder [--project <project>] [--workspace <workspace>] [--verbose] [--dry-run] <folder-path> --group <group> --targets <targets> ...

ARGUMENTS:
  <folder-path>           Path to the folder to add

OPTIONS:
  -p, --project <project> Path to .xcodeproj file (default: looks for
                          *.xcodeproj in current directory)
  -w, --workspace <workspace>
                          Path to .xcworkspace file
  -V, --verbose           Enable verbose output with performance metrics
  --dry-run               Preview changes without saving
  -g, --group <group>     Group to add the folder to
  -t, --targets <targets> Target names to add folder to
  --version               Show the version.
  -h, --help              Show help information.

